I. want. to. eat. at. Cilantro. every. single. day.  Cilantro is the most delicious, fresh, affordable meal in the neighborhood. This is a truly authentic, locally owned restaurant that puts love in the food and care into the customer service experience. The staff is warm and welcoming and I always love talking with them. If something's not right, let them know and they'll help you out. Ask them about their favorite items! Ask them how their dishes are made!  Great place to go with coworkers.  I'm always amazed that you can get such authentic Mediterranean food so close to the Inner Harbor. My favorite dish is the chicken or lamb shawarma platter with lots of toppings and vegetables. You have to check out their unlimited toppings like hummus, baba ganough (insanely tasty eggplant dip) and pickles.  I've had dreams about their lafa bread - no joke, it's that good!  Mu husband has a lot of dietary restrictions, but Cilantro has options for everyone. There are even gluten free, vegetarian, pescatarian, vegan and carnivorous choices. Don't forget dessert. The chocolate mousse is creamy and chocolatey without being overpowering. It's not expensive, but feels like a decadent treat.  [ brb going to cilantro ]
